</link>		<yourcomment>    OK. It looks like you've fallen for the old Remoting 2.0 Trap. With version 1.0, the files were actually in the folder path of Flash MX. With version 2.0 they packaged the files inside components. The files are there, but not the way you think they should be. With Remoting 2.0 you need to open your Window &gt; Other Panels &gt; Common Libraries &gt; Remoting panel and drag those to your stage. And if you need to get the actual files, you can get them from the Macromedia site as well.  </yourcomment>		<date>{ts '2005-03-01 15:15:14'}</date>		<formatteddate>01, March 2005</formatteddate>		<publish>1</publish>	</comment>
