    &lt;p&gt;Thanks for your comment leif, but maybe you clarify something for me.&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;So what you are saying is that in version 2 you need to drag the components onto your stage and then compile the movie? What strikes me as odd is that I thought I'd been running the same version of MX pro for the best part of a year. So somewhere in between did MM update MX pro to be that different (I remember there being an updater)? Also having now copied over the what are essentially version 1 components, how will this affect my development environment? I guess this mean that if I don't drag the components onto the stage version 1 components will be used.&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;Not to rant on about this, but MM are a strange ship. With CFMX change is introduced with every effort for backward compatibility, but it seems that with the Flash range of products it's the complete opposite. Then again I am something of a beginner with Flash so maybe I just not aware/don't know where to look for that kind of information.&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;Thanks for the comment, I'll update the post asap.&lt;/p&gt;

